issue.title: Improve clean setup process
issue.body:
Currently, the install script in this repo is only a small part of setting up a new machine. Ideally, I'd like this to automate numerous other tasks:

## Simple additions
- [ ] Set up the `bin` repository & linking
- [ ] Actually perform the symlinking, not just print the commands
- [ ] Generate SSH keys (e.g. `ssh-keygen -t ed25519`)

## Set up Homebrew
- [ ] iterm2 (preconfigure `PrefsCustomFolder` plist entry)
- [ ] google-cloud-sdk
- [ ] docker
- [ ] php latest
- [ ] rectangle
- [ ] ripgrep
- [ ] others?

## System settings [`~/Library/Preferences/GlobalPreferences.plist`]
(https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/87619/where-are-keyboard-shortcuts-stored-for-backup-and-sync-purposes)
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts for changing tabs 
```xml
	<key>NSUserKeyEquivalents</key>
	<dict>
		<key>Select Next Tab</key>
		<string>@~→</string>
		<key>Select Previous Tab</key>
		<string>@~←</string>
		<key>Show Next Tab</key>
		<string>@~→</string>
		<key>Show Previous Tab</key>
		<string>@~←</string>
	</dict>
```
- [ ] Rebind capslock to escape: https://stackoverflow.com/a/37648516
- [ ] Disable various autocorrect
```xml
	<key>NSAutomaticCapitalizationEnabled</key>
	<false/>
<!-- etc -->
```
- [ ] Disable some trackpad gestures
- [ ] Dark mode?
- [ ] Safari: turn on dev mode (`com.apple.Safari IncludeDevelopMenu -bool true`..plus other things?)

It looks like a lot of the plist hackery can be done via `defaults write`

e.g. `defaults write .GlobalPreferences NSUserKeyEquivalents -dict-add "Show Next Tab" "@~\\U2192"` seems to put the right value into settings, although it doesn't (immediately?) take effect.

- [ ] Mission Control > Displays have separate spaces (fixes annoying dock behavior on multi monitor setup)

While this isn't designed for a niche use-case, there are some specific assumptions that aren't super well-documented at this time:

- Multiple stages (implied by the name, but still...), such as dependency builds

Trying to use this without those conditions being met will at best be pointless, so clarifying those expectations in the readme will be valuable.

issue.title: Improve default configuration of PHP extensions
issue.body:
In the past, I've leveraged the behavior of PHP ini files interpreting environment variables to make configuration of extensions relatively straightforward (e.g. `PHP_OPCACHE_PRELOAD=""` & `opcache.preload=${PHP_OPCACHE_PRELOAD}`)

Having similar functionality in the project template makes this behavior more accessible and discoverable, not to mention is an improved opportunity to provide some useful and performant defaults.

issue.title: APK add optimizations
issue.body:
Explore improvements to the dockerfile where (at minimum) `$PHPIZE_DEPS` are installed as a virtual package and removed in the same step as the relevant PECL pieces.

I've observed a >200MB reduction in layer size by doing this (which is massive given the ~70MB Alpine base), although it needs to be applied thoughtfully since dev libraries (e.g. `libmemcached-dev`) seem to be dynamically linked and if they're removed you'll get startup errors.

Before:
```Dockerfile
RUN apk add --update --no-cache $PHPIZE_DEPS
```

```
        "Size": 301840265,
        "VirtualSize": 301840265,
<missing>      8 seconds ago   RUN /bin/sh -c apk add --update --no-cache -…   228MB     buildkit.dockerfile.v0
```

After:
```Dockerfile
# Install extensions with dependencies
ENV PECL_EXTENSIONS="memcached"
RUN apk add --update --no-cache --virtual .phpize $PHPIZE_DEPS \
  && apk add --update --no-cache \
    libmemcached-dev \
    libzip-dev \
  && pecl install $PECL_EXTENSIONS \
  && docker-php-ext-enable $PECL_EXTENSIONS \
  && pecl clear-cache \
  && apk del .phpize
```
```
        "Size": 79385518,
        "VirtualSize": 79385518,
<missing>      36 seconds ago   RUN /bin/sh -c apk add --update --no-cache -…   5.96MB    buildkit.dockerfile.v0
```

This needs some experimentation for usability, but I've had an initial positive experience with some local projects.

issue.title: Allow environment vars to default to other env vars
issue.body:
When trying to create config values for overrides/defaults, it can become tedious and distracting to build all of the logic inside of a definition closure.

```php
  'db_primary' => env('DB_PRIMARY'),
  'DB_REPLICA' => env('DB_REPLICA', null),
  'db_replica' => fn ($c) => $c->get('DB_REPLICA') ?? $c->get('db_primary'),
```

Instead, inline would be clearer and less error-prone:

```php
  'db_primary' => env('DB_PRIMARY'),
  'db_replica' => env('DB_REPLICA', env('DB_PRIMARY')),
```

issue.body:
Currently, the install script in this repo is only a small part of setting up a new machine. Ideally, I'd like this to automate numerous other tasks:

## Simple additions
- [ ] Set up the `bin` repository & linking
- [ ] Actually perform the symlinking, not just print the commands
- [ ] Generate SSH keys (e.g. `ssh-keygen -t ed25519`)

## Set up Homebrew
- [ ] iterm2 (preconfigure `PrefsCustomFolder` plist entry)
- [ ] google-cloud-sdk
- [ ] docker
- [ ] php latest
- [ ] rectangle
- [ ] ripgrep
- [ ] others?

## System settings [`~/Library/Preferences/GlobalPreferences.plist`]
(https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/87619/where-are-keyboard-shortcuts-stored-for-backup-and-sync-purposes)
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts for changing tabs 
```xml
	<key>NSUserKeyEquivalents</key>
	<dict>
		<key>Select Next Tab</key>
		<string>@~→</string>
		<key>Select Previous Tab</key>
		<string>@~←</string>
		<key>Show Next Tab</key>
		<string>@~→</string>
		<key>Show Previous Tab</key>
		<string>@~←</string>
	</dict>
```
- [ ] Rebind capslock to escape: https://stackoverflow.com/a/37648516
- [ ] Disable various autocorrect
```xml
	<key>NSAutomaticCapitalizationEnabled</key>
	<false/>
<!-- etc -->
```
- [ ] Disable some trackpad gestures
- [ ] Dark mode?
- [ ] Safari: turn on dev mode (`com.apple.Safari IncludeDevelopMenu -bool true`..plus other things?)

It looks like a lot of the plist hackery can be done via `defaults write`

e.g. `defaults write .GlobalPreferences NSUserKeyEquivalents -dict-add "Show Next Tab" "@~\\U2192"` seems to put the right value into settings, although it doesn't (immediately?) take effect.

- [ ] Mission Control > Displays have separate spaces (fixes annoying dock behavior on multi monitor setup)

issue.title: Improve default configuration of PHP extensions
issue.body:
In the past, I've leveraged the behavior of PHP ini files interpreting environment variables to make configuration of extensions relatively straightforward (e.g. `PHP_OPCACHE_PRELOAD=""` & `opcache.preload=${PHP_OPCACHE_PRELOAD}`)

Having similar functionality in the project template makes this behavior more accessible and discoverable, not to mention is an improved opportunity to provide some useful and performant defaults.

issue.title: APK add optimizations
issue.body:
Explore improvements to the dockerfile where (at minimum) `$PHPIZE_DEPS` are installed as a virtual package and removed in the same step as the relevant PECL pieces.

I've observed a >200MB reduction in layer size by doing this (which is massive given the ~70MB Alpine base), although it needs to be applied thoughtfully since dev libraries (e.g. `libmemcached-dev`) seem to be dynamically linked and if they're removed you'll get startup errors.

Before:
```Dockerfile
RUN apk add --update --no-cache $PHPIZE_DEPS
```

```
        "Size": 301840265,
        "VirtualSize": 301840265,
<missing>      8 seconds ago   RUN /bin/sh -c apk add --update --no-cache -…   228MB     buildkit.dockerfile.v0
```

After:
```Dockerfile
# Install extensions with dependencies
ENV PECL_EXTENSIONS="memcached"
RUN apk add --update --no-cache --virtual .phpize $PHPIZE_DEPS \
  && apk add --update --no-cache \
    libmemcached-dev \
    libzip-dev \
  && pecl install $PECL_EXTENSIONS \
  && docker-php-ext-enable $PECL_EXTENSIONS \
  && pecl clear-cache \
  && apk del .phpize
```
```
        "Size": 79385518,
        "VirtualSize": 79385518,
<missing>      36 seconds ago   RUN /bin/sh -c apk add --update --no-cache -…   5.96MB    buildkit.dockerfile.v0
```

This needs some experimentation for usability, but I've had an initial positive experience with some local projects.

issue.title: Allow environment vars to default to other env vars
issue.body:
When trying to create config values for overrides/defaults, it can become tedious and distracting to build all of the logic inside of a definition closure.

```php
  'db_primary' => env('DB_PRIMARY'),
  'DB_REPLICA' => env('DB_REPLICA', null),
  'db_replica' => fn ($c) => $c->get('DB_REPLICA') ?? $c->get('db_primary'),
```

Instead, inline would be clearer and less error-prone:

```php
  'db_primary' => env('DB_PRIMARY'),
  'db_replica' => env('DB_REPLICA', env('DB_PRIMARY')),
```

issue.body:
Currently, the install script in this repo is only a small part of setting up a new machine. Ideally, I'd like this to automate numerous other tasks:

## Simple additions
- [ ] Set up the `bin` repository & linking
- [ ] Actually perform the symlinking, not just print the commands
- [ ] Generate SSH keys (e.g. `ssh-keygen -t ed25519`)

## Set up Homebrew
- [ ] iterm2 (preconfigure `PrefsCustomFolder` plist entry)
- [ ] google-cloud-sdk
- [ ] docker
- [ ] php latest
- [ ] rectangle
- [ ] ripgrep
- [ ] others?

## System settings [`~/Library/Preferences/GlobalPreferences.plist`]
(https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/87619/where-are-keyboard-shortcuts-stored-for-backup-and-sync-purposes)
- [ ] Keyboard shortcuts for changing tabs 
```xml
	<key>NSUserKeyEquivalents</key>
	<dict>
		<key>Select Next Tab</key>
		<string>@~→</string>
		<key>Select Previous Tab</key>
		<string>@~←</string>
		<key>Show Next Tab</key>
		<string>@~→</string>
		<key>Show Previous Tab</key>
		<string>@~←</string>
	</dict>
```
- [ ] Rebind capslock to escape: https://stackoverflow.com/a/37648516
- [ ] Disable various autocorrect
```xml
	<key>NSAutomaticCapitalizationEnabled</key>
	<false/>
<!-- etc -->
```
- [ ] Disable some trackpad gestures
- [ ] Dark mode?
- [ ] Safari: turn on dev mode (`com.apple.Safari IncludeDevelopMenu -bool true`..plus other things?)

It looks like a lot of the plist hackery can be done via `defaults write`

e.g. `defaults write .GlobalPreferences NSUserKeyEquivalents -dict-add "Show Next Tab" "@~\\U2192"` seems to put the right value into settings, although it doesn't (immediately?) take effect.

issue.title: Improve default configuration of PHP extensions
issue.body:
In the past, I've leveraged the behavior of PHP ini files interpreting environment variables to make configuration of extensions relatively straightforward (e.g. `PHP_OPCACHE_PRELOAD=""` & `opcache.preload=${PHP_OPCACHE_PRELOAD}`)

Having similar functionality in the project template makes this behavior more accessible and discoverable, not to mention is an improved opportunity to provide some useful and performant defaults.

issue.title: APK add optimizations
issue.body:
Explore improvements to the dockerfile where (at minimum) `$PHPIZE_DEPS` are installed as a virtual package and removed in the same step as the relevant PECL pieces.

I've observed a >200MB reduction in layer size by doing this (which is massive given the ~70MB Alpine base), although it needs to be applied thoughtfully since dev libraries (e.g. `libmemcached-dev`) seem to be dynamically linked and if they're removed you'll get startup errors.

Before:
```Dockerfile
RUN apk add --update --no-cache $PHPIZE_DEPS
```

```
        "Size": 301840265,
        "VirtualSize": 301840265,
<missing>      8 seconds ago   RUN /bin/sh -c apk add --update --no-cache -…   228MB     buildkit.dockerfile.v0
```

After:
```Dockerfile
# Install extensions with dependencies
ENV PECL_EXTENSIONS="memcached"
RUN apk add --update --no-cache --virtual .phpize $PHPIZE_DEPS \
  && apk add --update --no-cache \
    libmemcached-dev \
    libzip-dev \
  && pecl install $PECL_EXTENSIONS \
  && docker-php-ext-enable $PECL_EXTENSIONS \
  && pecl clear-cache \
  && apk del .phpize
```
```
        "Size": 79385518,
        "VirtualSize": 79385518,
<missing>      36 seconds ago   RUN /bin/sh -c apk add --update --no-cache -…   5.96MB    buildkit.dockerfile.v0
```

This needs some experimentation for usability, but I've had an initial positive experience with some local projects.

issue.title: Allow environment vars to default to other env vars
issue.body:
When trying to create config values for overrides/defaults, it can become tedious and distracting to build all of the logic inside of a definition closure.

```php
  'db_primary' => env('DB_PRIMARY'),
  'DB_REPLICA' => env('DB_REPLICA', null),
  'db_replica' => fn ($c) => $c->get('DB_REPLICA') ?? $c->get('db_primary'),
```

Instead, inline would be clearer and less error-prone:

```php
  'db_primary' => env('DB_PRIMARY'),
  'db_replica' => env('DB_REPLICA', env('DB_PRIMARY')),
```
